This directory contains scripts providing functions deemed useful across a broad 
spectrum of customers.

Although Apache Design Solutions, Inc., provides these scripts at no charge as an 
aid to our customers, there is no guarantee for support in resolving customer issues 
found running the scripts nor any guarantee for continuation of these scripts in 
future releases of RedHawk(TM).

+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
+
+ rh_setup.pl  quick setup utility for RedHawk
+


SYNOPSIS

  Helps to setup necessary input files for static and dynamic runs of RedHawk

DESCRIPTION

  rh_setup.pl creates all the files needed to launch Redhawk simulation, either
  static or dynamic:

  <design>.gsr     - global settings
  run_static.tcl   - static run script
  run_dynamic.tcl  - dynamic run script
  run_setupApl.tcl - script for setting up design dependent APL run

  Every parameter value in generated <design>.gsr can come from 4 sources in the 
  following precedence:
   a. From rh_setup.pl command line parameters
   b. From parameters of previous invocation of rh_setup.pl saved in rh_setup.init
      file
   c. From template gsr pointed by variable $APACHEDA_TEMPLATE_GSR, if this
      file exists
   d. From default value preset by Apache

  Input to the script is incremental. You can invoke the script with one or more 
  command line arguments. Script will prompt you if any of the required arguments
  are missing (for ex. power net name) Re-invoke the script adding/changing the 
  arguments, until all required information is complete.

  Unix wildcards are accepted for options which specify file names. For example
  '-def *def */*def */*/*def' will match all the def files up to 2 levels down
  If the file with the same name is found more than once in the search pattern,
  the first occurance will be picked.

  Then rh_setup.pl checks, that all input files exist and creates all configuration
  files listed above.

  To launch simulation run:
  'redhawk -f run_static.tcl' or 'redhawk -f run_dynamic.tcl'


  Required parameters:
  ---------------------------------
  -top_cell 
	Top module of design hierarchy for this analysis
	Ex: TOP    Default: none
  -vdd_nets 
	Names of power nets used in this analysis along with nominal voltages
	Ex: VDD 1.1 VDDO 2.0    Default: none
  -vss_nets 
	Names of ground nets used in this analysis
	Ex: VSS VSSO    Default: none
  -frequency 
	Primary operating frequency of this design (Hz)
	Ex: 100e6    Default: none
  -tech_file 
	Apache tech file with dielectrics, metal layers
	Ex: apache.tech    Default: ../design_data/tech/*.tech ../../data/tech/apache.tech
  -lef_files 
	LEF files for technology,library cells, hierarchical and IP blocks
	Ex: stdlib/*.lef macros/{A,B}.lef    Default: none
  -def_files 
	DEF files for top module, hierarchical and IP blocks
	Ex: def/*def    Default: none
  -lib_files 
	Synopsys Liberty format (.lib) timing libraries
	Ex: /home/libs/*lib    Default: none
  -pad_files 
	Apache PLOC file that gives X,Y of ideal Voltage sources
	For block level analysis you can use keyword 'def_pins'. This forces Redhawk
	to place one pad in the center of every VDD/VSS pin described in top-level
	def file.  
	Ex: top.ploc or def_pins keyword    Default: none

  Optional parameters:
  ---------------------------------
  -spf_files 
	Hierarchical SPEF or DSPF files of post-layout parasitics
	Ex: top.spef block.dspf    Default: none
  -sta_files 
	Timing files from STA
	Ex: timing/top.timing    Default: none
  -pgarc_file 
	Custom PGARC definition file. Defines VDD to VSS paths 
	if you have multiple grounds
	Ex: custom_cell.pgarc    Default: none
  -apl_files 
	Apache cell.current file of current profiles from apl run
	Ex: apl/cell.current    Default: 
  -aplcap_files 
	Apache cell.cdev decap file from apl -c run
	Ex: apl/cell.cdev    Default: none
  -gds_dirs 
	Load all lef/def/lib files created by gds2def/gdsmem in specified directories
	Ex: data/gdsmem data/gdsdef    Default: {
}
  -avm_conf 
	Config file for 'on the fly' rule-based memory characterization
	Ex: ram64x15.conf    Default: none
  -avg_pwr 
	Average chip power (watt). If defined, all instance toggle rates are
	scaled to bring the total chip power to a requested level
	Ex: 0.8    Default: none
  -input_slew 
	Default input slew of all cells
	Ex: 20ps    Default: 200ps
  -toggle_rate 
	Default uniform activity level of this design
	Ex: 0.3    Default: none
  -iosso 
	Create iosso teplate and run_iosso.tcl
	Ex: on, off    Default: off
  -all_in_gsr 
	If 'on', all input lef/def/lib files are listed directly in GSR. If 'off'
	, <design>.{lefs,defs,libs} list files will be created and GSR will
	point to these files
	Ex: on, off    Default: on

+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
+
+apl_std_setup.pl   Performs setup for APL and APLCAP characterization of std. cells in the design
+

DESCRIPTION
 apl_std_setup.pl generates the configuration file required for APL 
 and runs APL to generate cell.current and cell.cdev

 Script accepts user options from 2 sources:
 a. from $cwd/apl_std_setup.init file
 b. from command line arguments, which are saved as well in extract_gds.init by the script

 Input to the script is incremental. The user may invoke the script with one or more options, then re-invoke 
the script adding more information, until all required information is complete. The user may add optional 
information at any time.

OPTIONS
  -vdd_value
    Value of supply voltage
  -vdd_pin
    Name of the VDD pin in SPICE netlist
  -vss_pin
    Name of the VSS pin in SPICE netlist
  -temperature
    Analysis temperature in C
  -spice_netlist
    List of SPICE netlist files
  -device_model
    File containing device model library
  -corner
    Analysis corner
  -rise_slew_threshold
    Rise slew thresholds used in STA
  -fall_slew_threshold
    Rise slew thresholds used in STA
  -gsr_file
    GSR file used for analysis
  -apl_setup_dir
    
  -cell_list
    List of cells to be characterized

