+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
+
+create_spi_ploc.pl  
+

Usage:
 perl create_spi_ploc.pl -ploc <ploc file> -Rhigh -Rmed -Rlow -Chigh -Cmed -Clow \
    -wbpwr <Rw> <Lw> <Cw> -wbgnd <Rw> <Lw> <Cw> -pkgpwr <Rpkg> <Lpkg> <Cpkg> \
    -pkggnd <Rpkg> <Lpkg> <Cpkg> -vdd -vss -volts

 Available options 
 PLEASE ENTER THE R,L,C in Ohm,Henry,Farad respectively
-ploc	ploc file(REQUIRED)
-Rmed	default ( 1e-3 ohms)
-Rhigh	default ( 0.1 ohms)
-Rlow	default ( 1e-5 ohms) 
-Cmed	default ( 1pF)
-Chigh	default ( 5pF)
-Clow	default (0.1pF)
-wbpwr	 <Rw> <Lw> <Cw>
-wbgnd	 <Rw> <Lw> <Cw>
-pkgpwr	 <Rpkg> <Lpkg> <Cpkg>
-pkggnd	 <Rpkg> <Lpkg> <Cpkg>
Default Rpkg=1e-3,Cpkg=10e-12,Lpkg=10e-9
Default Rw=1e-3, Cpkg=10e-12,Lpkg=10e-9
-vdd	default VDD
-volts	defaut(VDD=1.0V)
-vss	default VSS

+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
+
+decap2eco.pl  Apache decap ECO to Synopsys Scheme translation
+

USAGE: decap2eco.pl [ -h ] <decap_file> <cellsize_file>
       -h     - show this help message and exit

**** IMPORTANT NOTES ****
1.   The cellsize file is needed so that the correct placement command
     in scheme can be created.  The cell size file should have this format:

     <cellname> <xsize_in_um> <ysize_in_um>

     For example:

     decap1 8.8 4.6

2.   The default output files will be decap.eco and decap.scm.

+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
+
+gds_setup.pl   Generates configuration files and runs gds2def extraction for multiple cells
+


DESCRIPTION

 Script accepts user options from 2 sources:
 a. from $cwd/gds_setup.init file
 b. from command line arguments, which are saved as well in gds_setup.init by the script

 Input to the script is incremental. The user may invoke the script with one or more options, 
then re-invoke the script adding more information, until all required information is complete. 
The user may add optional information at any time.

Script examines lef and gds files first to ensure that cells being extracted have both gds 
and lef description

 Example:

 perl gds_setup.pl -vdd VDD vdd vddx vddy, VDD_SOC \
              -vss VSS gnd vss \
              -map gds_layer.map \
              -cell MEM22x64 MEM22x32 \
              -lef_files lef_dir/*.lef \
              -gds_files gds_dir/*.gds \
              -mem on \
              -norun on

OPTIONS
  -vdd_nets
	VDD net names separated with ',' Multiple GDS labels can map to a single VDD net
	Default: none
	Example: 'VDD vdda vddb, VDD_SOC' - segments labeled in GDS with 'vdda' and 'vddb' will 
        appear as 'VDD' in generated def file. 'VDD_SOC' will bot be renamed
  -vss_nets
	VSS net names. Same syntax as VDD
	Default: none
  -cell_names
	List of cell names for GDS conversion or name of the file where cells are listed
	Default: all non CORE macros found in specified lef files
  -map_file
	GDS layer map file
	Default: none
  -lef_files
	LEF files of macros to be extracted
	Default: ../lef/*.lef
  -gds_files
	GDS files to be extracted
	Default: ../gds/*.gds
  -mem
	Run gdsmem  (on/off)
	Default: off
  -start_layer
	Extraction starting layer
	Default: none
	Example: m1
  -core_start_layer
	Core extraction starting layer
	Default: none
	Example: m3
  -options_file
	File containing list of additional gds2def options to use
	Default: none
  -norun
	Setting to 'on' will stop the script after creation of config files 
	Default: off


