+
+ lec2rh.pl  convert LEC Mapping file from Conformal/Verplex to RedHawk readable mapping file
+

To learn more about the options, use -help or -man to display the man page.

Usage:
    lec2rh.pl -in ARGUMENT -def TOP LEVEL DEF -div <hierarchy_separator>
    -lef_dir LEF_DIR -q_pin <output_pin of the flop> [OPTIONS]

    ARGUMENT: LEC(Logic Equivalency Check) Mapping file from Conformal

    TOP LEVEL DEF: design top level def file

    LEF_DIR: Directory with all the LEF files for macros and memories

    -q_pin: Specify the output pin of the flop(whether q or qn default=q)

    -div : Specify the hierarchy separator(default: obtained from Top level
    DEF)

    OPTIONS: -h, -help, -man, -o

    outputs --> "o' (default is lec2rh.rpt)

