+
+ analyse_RH_run.tcl   Documentation provided in Report_Generation_Scripts_ReadMe.pdf
+ 
+


+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
+
+ cpm2spice.pl  Automated creation of SPICE deck to generate Rdie/Cdie frequency spread for a CPM model
+ 
+
Usage:
    cpm2spice.pl [options] arguments

    Options: -h, -help, -man, -verbose -debug

    Arguments: -cpm cpm_input_file, -sp spice_output_file

Options:
    -h  Prints a short synopsis.

    -help
        Prints a synopsis and a description of program options and
        arguments.

    -man
        Prints the entire man page.

    -debug
        Prints debug info to the log.

    -verbose
        Prints verbose debug/log info.

Arguments:
    -cpm cpm_input_file
        The path to the input CPM model.

    -sp spice_output_file
        The path to the output SPICE deck. Don't forget to edit the
        simulation parameters!


+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
+
+ mmx.tbc   tcl script containing utilities for Redhawk-MMX/Totem
+
+
Usage:
Append $APACHEROOT/scripts to your path. (ex) set path = ($APACHEROOT/scripts $path)
source mmx.tbc in Redhawk/Totem command window.
The following commands are available in Redhawk/Totem command window.

mmx_add_decap_cell            - to place decap cells over a wide region
mmx_change_decap              - to change esc of intentional decap xtors in a region
mmx_clear                     - to clear GUI screen
mmx_dump_dvd                  - to dump out the whole DVD waveforms
mmx_help                      - to show available commands
mmx_plot_histogram            - to plot a histogram of DVD result
mmx_plot_resistance_histogram - to plot a histogram of gridcheck result
mmx_show_decap                - to show intentional decap xtors
mmx_show_lef_pin              - to show lef pins in <>_adsgds1.lef
mmx_show_missing_via          - to show missing vias
mmx_show_xtor                 - to show xtors based on SPF location and lef location


Description:
mmx_add_decap_cell 
                -region <llx lly urx ury>
                -pg <power> <ground>
                -metal <name>
                ?-cap <value>?
                ?-res <value>?
                ?-leakage <value>?
                ?-nc <value>?
                ?-nt <value>?
                ?-hws <value>?
                ?-mode <h/v>?
                ?-place?

                # -nc : to specify # of decap cells/rail (default: 10)
                # -nt : to set threshold value to find rails (default: 1)
                # -hws : to merge adjacent rails. hws = 0.5x(width+space) (default: 0.2)
                # -mode : to set wire direction (h-horizontal / v-vertical)
                # -place : to place decap cells

1. It shows P/G rails where decap cells can be placed (do not use -place here)
   mmx_add_decap_cell -region 100 100 200 200 -pg vdd vss -metal M1 -cap 10p
2. If the rails looks correct, use -place to really place decap
   mmx_add_decap_cell -region 100 100 200 200 -pg vdd vss -metal M1 -cap 10p -place


mmx_change_decap
                -pg <p1> <g1> ... -pg <pN> <gN>
                -region <llx1 lly1 urx1 ury1> ... -region <llxN llyN urxN uryN>
                ?-o <output_file>?
                ?-cap <c1> ... -cap <cN>?
                ?-res <r1> ... -res <rN>?
                ?-leakage <l1> ... -leakage <lN>?
                ?-change?
                ?-run?

                # possible format of cap/res/leakage : <value/#x/->
                # 'value' : F/ohm/A
                # '#x' : multiplied factor
                # '-'  : don't change
                # -change : to change cdev
                # -run : to change cdev and run dynamic analysis

1. It shows intentional decap xtors in region(100 100 200 200) and region (300 300 400 400)
   mmx_change_decap -pg vdd vss -pg vddq vssq -region 100 100 200 200 -region 300 300 400 400
2. If you want to triple the intentioanl decap
   mmx_change_decap -pg vdd vss -region 100 100 200 200 -o user.cdev -cap 3x -change
3. If you want to distribute 10pF
   mmx_change_decap -pg vdd vss -region 100 100 200 200 -cap 10p -change


mmx_clear
1. It clears the screen


mmx_dump_dvd
                -o <output_file>
                ?-index_range <from> <to>?
                ?-region <llx lly urx ury>?
                ?-time_base <time>?
                ?-nocap?
                ?-pwl?

                # -index_range : to dump waveforms only in the range (default: 0 ~ 999)
                # -time_base : to set the time base of waveforms
                # -nocap : to exclude decap xtors
                # -pwl : to generate pwl

1. It extracts the worst 1000 dvd waveforms into <>.ta0
   mmx_dump_dvd -o dvd.ta0


mmx_help
1. it shows all available mmx_* commands


mmx_plot_histogram
                ?-pg <net1> ... -pg <netN>?
                ?-bn <bin_number>?
                ?-bs <bin_size>?
                ?-min <min_voltage>?
                ?-max <max_voltage>?
                ?-o <output_file>?
                ?-type <dynamicVectorless/staticIR>?
                ?-log?

                # -log : to plot log of xtor counts

1. plot dynamic voltage drop histogram or static IR histogram
   mmx_plot_histogram
2. show usage
   mmx_plot_histogram -h 


mmx_plot_resistance_histogram
                ?-pg <pg1> ... -pg <pgN>?
                ?-bn <bin_number>?
                ?-bs <bin_size>?
                ?-min <min_%>?
                ?-max <max_%>?
                ?-o <output_file>?
                ?-log?

                # -log : to plot log of xtor counts

1. plot a histogram of gridcheck result
   mmx_plot_resistance_histogram
2. show usage
   mmx_plot_resistance_histogram -h 


mmx_show_decap
                -pg <p1> <g1> ... -pg <pN> <gN>
                ?-region <llx lly urx ury>?
                ?-name?
                ?-conn?
                ?-mono?

                # -name : to show decap names
                # -conn : to show pg connectivity
                # -mono : to use monochrome markers (faster)

1. show intentional xtors in a region
   mmx_show_decap -pg vdd vss -region 100 100 200 200
2. print xtor names and show connection between vdd and vss
   mmx_show_decap -pg vdd vss -region 100 100 200 200 -name -conn


mmx_show_lef_pin
		-dir <gdsmmx_dir>
                ?-cell <cell>?
                ?-inst <instance>?
                ?-region <llx lly urx ury>?

1. show lef pins in <>_adsgds1.lef
   mmx_show_lef_pin -dir ../gdsmmx


mmx_show_missing_via
                -range <minV> <maxV>
                ?-pg <net1> ... -pg <netN>?
                ?-gif <file_name>?

                # -range : to set the color range of voltage difference

1. show missing vias whose vdiff are over 1mV
   mmx_show_missing_via -range 1m 10m


mmx_show_xtor
                -pg <net1> ... -pg <netN>
		-dir <gdsmmx_dir>
                ?-region <llx lly urx ury>?
                ?-nocap?
                ?-n <value>?

                # -nocap : to hide decap xtors
                # -n : to set the max number of displayed xtors (default: 1000)

1. show xtors connected on vdd and vss
   mmx_show_xtor -pg vdd -pg vss -dir ../gdsmmx -region 100 100 200 200


+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
+
+ emi.tbc   tcl script containing utilities for on-chip emi analysis
+ 
+
Usage:
source emi.tbc in Redhawk/Totem command window.
The following commands are available in Redhawk/Totem command window.

emi_fft                       - to convert chip partition current to EMI data by FFT
emi_map                       - to display EMI map at specified frequency from EMI data
emi_plot                      - to display magnitude spectrum and current 
emi_gifs                      - to geneate GIF of EMI map
emi_movie                     - to display EMI movie from EMI data

Description:
emi_fft
                ?-min_f <freq>?
                ?-max_f <freq>?
                ?-step <freq>?
                ?-unit <fft result unit>?
                ?-power?
                ?-ground?
                ?-net <net1> ... <netN>?
                ?-di?

        Converts chip partition current to EMI data by FFT. Chip partition
        current is generated by using 'generate emi_current' with -nx -ny options

        Inputs:
        Chip partition current (adsRpt/Dynamic/emi_ivdd.<domain>)

        Outputs:
        FFT for each partition (fftTmp/*.temp)
        FFT for each frequency (emiRpt/data/emi_<net>_<freq>.dat)
        FFT Report (emiRpt/emi_<net>.rpt)

        Options:
        -min_f <freq> : Min frequency for FFT. Specify in Hz using scientific
        notation
        Example: -min_f 200M
        Default: 1/DYNAMIC_SIMULATION_TIME

        -max_f <freq> : Max frequency for FFT. Specify in Hz using scientific
        notation
        Default: 1/DYNAMIC_TIME_STEP

        -step <freq> : frequency step for FFT. Specify in Hz using scientific
        notation
        Default: 1/DYNAMIC_SIMULATION_TIME

        -unit <fft unit> : Units for output of fft. Accepted units are: mp
        (magnitude and phase), db (decibels), dbm (decibels referenced to 1e-3),
        dbu (db referenced to 1e-6).
        Example: -unit dbm
        Default: mp

        -power : Use chip partition current of all power nets
        -ground : Use chip partition current of all ground nets
        -net <net1> ... <netN> : Use chip partition current of the specified nets
        Default: -power -ground
	Example: -net vdd1 vdd2

        -di : Use <design>.partition.ipwr instead of emi_ivdd.<domain>


emi_map
                ?-min_f <frequency>?
                ?-max_f <frequency>?
                ?-f <frequency>?
                ?-min <display min value>?
                ?-max <display max value>?
                ?-power?
                ?-ground?
                ?-net <net1> ... <netN>?
                ?-di?
                ?-ng?
                ?-exdata?

        Inputs:
        EMI Data (emiRpt/data/emi_<net>_<freq>.dat)

        Options:
        -min_f/-max_f <freq> : Specifies the frequency range to display EMI map
        Default: -min_f/-max_f of emi_fft
        Example: -min_f 200M -max_f 1G

        -f <freq> : Specifies the frequency to display EMI map
        If -f is used, -min_f/-max_f are ignored
        Example: -f 200M

        -min/-max <display value> : Min/Max value used for EMI map display

        -power : Display EMI map of all power nets
        -ground : Display EMI map of all ground nets
        -net <net1> ... <netN> : Display EMI map of the specified nets
        Default: -power -ground
        Example: -net vdd1 vdd2

        -di : Use 'emi_fft -di' results

        -ng : Not display partition grid

        -exdata : Use existing data from previous emi_fft run


emi_plot
                ?-p <px1><py1> ... -p <pxN><pyN>?
                ?-xy <x1><y1> ... -xy <xN><yN>?
                ?-s or -spectrum?
                ?-c or -current?
                ?-sv?
                ?-net <net1> ... <netN>?
                ?-di?
                ?-ng?
                ?-exdata?

        Inputs:
        EMI Data (emiRpt/data/emi_<net>_<freq>.dat)

        Options:
        -p <px> <py> : Select regions by partition numbers
        Example: -p 3 4 -p 10 7
        -xy <x> <y> : Select regions including the points
        Example: -xy 100 300 -xy 150 -100

        -spectrum : Show magnitude spectrum of the region
        -current : Show current waveforms of the region

        -sv : Use sv instead of xgraph

        -net <net1> ... <netN> : Include data of the specified nets
        Default: Include data of all power/ground nets
        Example: -net vdd1 vdd2

        -di : Use <design>.partition.ipwr instead of emi_ivdd.<domain>

        -ng : Not display partition grid

        -exdata : Use existing data from previous emi_fft run


emi_movie
                ?-d <frame delay>?
                ?-min_f <frequency>?
                ?-max_f <frequency>?
                ?-step <frequency>?
                ?-min <display min value>?
                ?-max <display max value>?
                ?-power?
                ?-ground?
                ?-net <net1> ... <netN>?
                ?-di?
                ?-exdata?

        Inputs:
        EMI Data (emiRpt/data/emi_<net>_<freq>.dat)

        Options:
        -d <movie frame delay in sec> : Specifies the delay for each frame in
        the movie. Default is 0

        -min_f/-max_f/-step <freq> : Specifies the frequency range to display EMI movie
        Default: -min_f/-max_f of emi_fft
        Example: -min_f 200M -max_f 1G

        -min/-max <display value> : Min/Max value used for EMI map display

        -power : Display EMI movie of all power nets
        -ground : Display EMI movie of all ground nets
        -net <net1> ... <netN> : Display EMI movie of the specified nets
        Default: -power -ground
        Example: -net vdd1 vdd2

        -di : Use <design>.partition.ipwr instead of emi_ivdd.<domain>

        -exdata : Use existing data from previous emi_fft run


emi_gifs
                ?-min_f <frequency>?
                ?-max_f <frequency>?
                ?-step <frequency>?
                ?-min <display min value>?
                ?-max <display max value>?
                ?-power?
                ?-ground?
                ?-net <net1> ... <netN>?
                ?-di?
                ?-exdata?

        Inputs:
        EMI Data (emiRpt/data/emi_<net>_<freq>.dat)

        Outputs:
        GIF of EMI map at each frequency (emiRpt/gifs/emi<freq>.gif)

        Options:
        -min_f/-max_f/-step <freq> : Specifies the frequency range to make gifs
        Default: -min_f/-max_f of emi_fft
        Example: -min_f 200M -max_f 1G

        -min/-max <display value> : Min/Max value used for EMI map display

        -power : Make gifs of all power nets
        -ground : Make gifs of all ground nets
        -net <net1> ... <netN> : Make gifs of the specified nets
        Default: -power -ground
        Example: -net vdd1 vdd2

        -di : Use <design>.partition.ipwr instead of emi_ivdd.<domain>

        -exdata : Use existing data from previous emi_fft run


